text.section:
The Institute shall:
Provide classroom education and training for career and volunteer fire and rescue personnel, both at the Institute and throughout this State;
Cooperate with other agencies that provide training for fire and rescue personnel;
Train instructors;
Prepare or adopt materials for training fire and rescue personnel;
Develop new fire and rescue training techniques;
Develop and implement specialized courses in fire fighting, including industrial fire fighting;
Maintain statistics and records on fire and rescue education, training, and related matters;
Develop programs to inform the public about the tasks performed by fire and rescue personnel;
Establish guidelines for instructional material to school systems in the State concerning fire and rescue education;
Provide disaster training for fire and rescue personnel; and
Cooperate with the Maryland Institute for Emergency Medical Services Systems to provide basic training for rescue personnel and emergency medical technicians.
